href="#choose-distributors">Find distributors</a>.</li><li><a
href="#create-a-brewing-production-schedule">Create a brewing production schedule</a>.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-you-get-a-brewery-license class="question">How do you get a brewery license?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Every state has unique regulations and necessary permits for the sale of alcohol. To find out what licenses and permits you need, visit your state's small business website or contact the office of the small business development director.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-basic-equipment-do-you-need-to-start-a-brewery class="question">What basic equipment do you need to start a brewery?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li>A brewhouse.</li><li>Fermentation tanks.</li><li>Brite tanks.</li><li>1/2 barrel kegs.</li><li>A keg washing system.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-brewery-equipment-cost class="question">How much does brewery equipment cost?</h3><div
class="answer"><p><a
href="#brewery-equipment-costs">Brewery equipment costs</a> anywhere from $100.00 to $98,500.00 per piece, depending on what it is and what it does.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-a-brewery-make class="question">How much does a brewery make?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Brewery owners earn between $30,000.00 and $60,000.00 per year, according to our research. However, owners' earnings tend to increase with the size and scale of the brewery.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-long-does-it-take-to-brew-beer-in-a-microbrewery class="question">How long does it take to brew beer in a microbrewery?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>If you're starting a microbrew batch, you can expect it to take a minimum of two weeks to ferment, but quite possibly longer if you want to age the beer for maximum flavor.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-a-brewery-to-make-beer class="question">How much does it cost a brewery to make beer?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The costs of making beer differ brewery to brewery. You can calculate these costs by keeping track of the direct labor involved in making the beer, the direct material, and the overhead in an operating budget. Add these three rates together to find the costs your brewery will put into making the beer.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-contract-brewing class="question">What is contract brewing?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Contract brewing takes place when a company hires a brewery to make a package beer for their brand. Contract brewing is becoming increasingly popular and it is sometimes beneficial for breweries that need to secure more revenue to pay for their equipment.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-are-the-essential-things-to-look-for-in-a-brewery-location class="question">What are the essential things to look for in a brewery location?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li>Ceilings with a minimum of 12" clearance.</li><li>State-of-the-art plumbing and electrical systems to hook your equipment into.</li><li>Proper floor drainage for spills and washing equipment.</li><li>Sealed and acid-resistant floors that don't break down from contact with chemicals.</li><li>Good ventilation to remove steam from the building when your brew kettle is boiling.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-the-difference-between-microbrewery-and-craft-brewery class="question">What is the difference between microbrewery and craft brewery?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>In brewing terms, "micro" refers to size while "craft" refers to style. A microbrewery is a small brewery that produces less than 15,000 barrels per year. A craft brewery is independently owned, produces less than 2 million gallons of beer per year, and uses at least 50% traditional malt.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-are-the-top-5-books-to-read-before-starting-a-brewery class="question">What are the top 5 books to read before starting a brewery?</h3><div
class="answer"><ol><li>"The Brewers Association’s Guide to Starting Your Own Brewery" by Dick Cantwell.</li><li>"Brewing Up a Business: Adventures in Beer from the Founder of Dogfish Head Craft Brewery" by Sam Calagione.</li><li>"Brewery Operations Manual" by Tom Hennessy.</li><li>"So You Want to Start a Brewery?: The Lagunitas Story" by Tony Magee.</li><li>"Beer Law: What Brewers Need to Know" by John Szymankiewicz.</li></ol></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-start-a-microbrewery class="question">How do I start a microbrewery?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Follow our <a
href="#how-to-start-a-brewery">step-by-step guide</a> to set up and open your microbrewery.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=do-most-breweries-start-small class="question">Do most breweries start small?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Some breweries begin as very small operations and then expand as money comes in, while others start on a large scale right away thanks to major outside investment. You can use the steps in our detailed guide to starting a brewery either way, but our advice is geared toward someone who wants to know how to start a small brewery.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-write-a-brewery-business-plan class="question">How do I write a brewery business plan?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>A business plan for a brewery should include the following items:</p><ul><li>Executive summary.</li><li>Business description.</li><li>Operations and management structure.</li><li>Marketing plan.</li><li>Competition analysis.</li><li>Financial data.</li><li>Future goals.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-should-i-include-in-my-brewery-startup-costs class="question">What should I include in my brewery startup costs?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li>Business registration and trademarking fees.</li><li>Leasing or purchasing a property.</li><li>Outfitting your property with the necessary equipment.</li><li>Obtaining a Brewer's Notice from the Alcohol and Tobacco Tax and Trade Bureau.</li><li>State license fees.</li><li>Hiring and training staff.</li><li>Getting in ingredients to start brewing.</li><li>Distributor fees to move the finished product.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=where-can-i-find-a-brewery-checklist class="question">Where can I find a brewery checklist?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>You can use our <a
href="#how-to-start-a-brewery">step-by-step guide</a>, which includes a number of free downloadable templates, including a checklist, when starting your brewery.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-you-start-a-brewery-with-no-money class="question">How do you start a brewery with no money?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>It is virtually impossible to start a brewery with no money, due to the space, equipment, and ingredients needed. However, if you start small and create a great recipe, you can start building a following by going to beer festivals and offering samples. A strong following, along with a solid business plan, will help you to gain investors so that your brewery can take off.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=where-can-i-find-a-brewery-production-schedule-template class="question">Where can I find a brewery production schedule template?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>You can use our free brewery production schedule template to help you create your own spreadsheet.</p></div></div></div></div></div> <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does it cost to open a brewery?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Brewery start-up costs depend on the initial size of the brewery. Microbrewery startup costs can range from $100,000.00 to over $1 million, according to our research. If you are wondering how to start a brewery with no money, it is virtually impossible since you need so much equipment.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I start a brewery legally?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#choose-a-name-and-trademark-it\">Choose a name<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#write-a-business-plan\">Create a business plan<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#find-a-location\">Find a location<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#form-a-legal-entity\">Form a legal entity<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#hire-employees\">Hire staff<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#get-a-license-from-the-ttb\">Get a Brewer's Notice from the TTB<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#get-state-licenses\">Obtain State licenses\/permits<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#choose-distributors\">Find distributors<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#create-a-brewing-production-schedule\">Create a brewing production schedule<\/a>.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you get a brewery license?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Every state has unique regulations and necessary permits for the sale of alcohol. To find out what licenses and permits you need, visit your state's small business website or contact the office of the small business development director.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What basic equipment do you need to start a brewery?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ul>\n<li>A brewhouse.<\/li>\n<li>Fermentation t